radiographic_examinations.findings: Fluid-filled appendix is dilated up to 10 mm with mucosal hyperemia and surrounding fat stranding compatible with acute appendicitis. Scattered appendicoliths measuring up to 3 mm within the lumen. Lung bases are clear, no pleural effusion, liver enhances homogeneously with no focal lesions, gallbladder is unremarkable, pancreas and kidneys without lesions, GI tract is normal, no evidence of perforation or abscess formation.
